one.name: Great Island
one.description: The ancient name of the island was Oilean Ard na Neimheadh, the "High (or important) island of Neimheadh".

three.name: Garnish Island
three.description: Garnish Island is a sort of paradisal place, resembling more of a Roman villa than an Irish island. Tucked into the pretty Bantry Bay of West Cork, Garnish Island is world-renowned for its divine gardens, alluring designs and rare specimens

four.name: The Skellig Islands
four.description: Most likely the most famous islands of Ireland on this list, the Skelligs are two scraggy rocks 13km off the Iveragh Peninsula. Considered a UNESCO World Heritage site, the Skelligs may be familiar as they are an important filming location for both the 2014 and 2017 Star Wars Films
